      <bioghist id="aspace_357a21831e4b03d6aa6a6588bd661e7c">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>James Allardyce Ewing was born in Fraserburgh, Scotland in 1857. He emigrated to Port Elizabeth, South Africa in 1877 and worked for Mackie, Dunn and Company. In 1890 he established the firm of J. A. Ewing and Company, with headquarters in London, and commercial interests in South Africa and Rhodesia. Ewing exercised great influence on the shipping and financial trade in South Africa. He died in 1924.</p>  
      </bioghist>
